ate of $\\frac{dM_{2}}{dt}=-\n1.61\\times{10^{-7}}M_\\odot/year$. The light curves of V1197 Her is reported to\nhave the O'Connell effect. Thus, a cool spot is added to the massive star to\nmodel the asymmetry on light curves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Aug 2019 06:32:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-05"}
