 expected, the accuracy of derived physical properties in MAGPHYS+photo-z\ndecreases strongly as redshift uncertainty increases. The all-in-one treatment\nof uncertainties afforded with this code is beneficial for accurately\ninterpreting physical properties of galaxies in large photometric datasets.\nFinally, we emphasize that MAGPHYS+photo-z is not intended to replace existing\nphoto-z codes, but rather offer flexibility to robustly interpret physical\nproperties when spectroscopic redshifts are unavailable. The MAGPHYS+photo-z\ncode is publicly available online.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Aug 2019 09:28:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-11"}
