of pile-up effects comparing the\ncurrently operating XMM-Newton with the planned Athena-WFI instrument. A\nsimulation of a galaxy cluster with the Athena- X-IFU shows the capability of\nSIXTE to predict the expected performance of an observation for a complex\nsource with a spatially varying spectrum and our current knowledge of the\nfuture instrument.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Aug 2019 10:01:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 8 Aug 2019 11:59:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
